From george Subject Re Toshiba CD ROM Any problems Mark Smith writes I'm thinking about getting a Toshiba CD ROM and hooking it up through the SCSI port on a Media Vision Pro Audio Spectrum sound Does anybody have this configuration out there If so does it work For anybody in general who has the Toshiba CD ROM drive have you had any hadware problems Door not opening scratched disks door not closing getting stuck or not closing all the way CD holder jamming and any other CD related I have one and it is my favorite CD ROM drive so I also have a NEC and have had experience with several other drives Various Phillips drives The is faster than the NEC I like its door better the NEC needs hands the XA handling The NEC needs to be re booted to go from XA to ROM while the does it on the fly All in all I am seriously considering replacing my NEC with another JWS